      <div class="about center">
        <h3>The Algorithim</h3>
        <p class="project__description">
          The main part of this project is the Wave Function Collapse algorithm.
          This algorithim works by having a user provide a set of tiles and a set
          of rules describing which tiles can neighbor each other. Then an empty
          grid, where every possible space can be any of the possible tiles, is
          created. A random tile within the group of tiles with the least amount
          of tile options is chosen and is collapsed to a random tile. Each tile
          is then recursively updated based on the defined rules, these two steps
          are repeated until every tile has been collapsed and the final image is
          generated and returned.
        </p>
      </div>

      

      <!-- Text Block -->
      <div class="about center">
        <h3>Technology</h3>
        <p class="project__description">
          The overall stack is built around Flask (Python), using HTML, Jinja,
          and Bootstrap to achieve a scalable site that still looks good. The site
          uses a custom callback system, where the back-end performs the request
          asynchronously, in the meantime the front-end continuously checks to
          see if the image has been generated. The entire app is encapsulated
          in a Docker container and finally hosted behind a NGINX reverse proxy
        </p>
      </div>

